passages.text: Fund inflows decline modestly/w but remain strong

Fund Flows: High- grade fund inflows decreased this week to \(\) 8.3bn\((- 18\% \text{WoW})\) , yet remain above the average YTD weekly inflow of \(\) 5.2bn\(. The decline was entirely led by Mutual Fund inflows which were down to\) \ \(2.4bn\) (- 51\% \text{WoW}) while ETF flows rose to \(\) 5.9bn\((+14\% \text{WoW})\) . Our estimate of flows to high- grade corporate bonds by the HG fund complex declined to \(+\) \(\) 3.8bn\((- 10\% \text{WoW})\) . All three sub- categories posted inflows this week: Corp- only fund inflows modestly increased to \(+\) \(\) 2.3bn\((+2\% \text{WoW})\) , while Aggregate funds and Total Return fund inflows decreased to \(+\) \(\) 3.8bn\((- 18\% \text{WoW})\) and \(+\) \(\) 2.2bn\((- 31\% \text{WoW})\) , respectively. Across the curve, Corp- only funds saw short- end outflows of \(\) 146mn\((- 124\% \text{WoW})\) , while intermediate and long end had inflows of \(+\) \(\) 1.1bn\((- 19\% \text{WoW})\) and \(+\) \(\) 1.4bn\((+343\% \text{WoW})\) , respectively. Within aggregate funds, the flows were focused on the intermediate bucket which saw inflows of \(+\) \(\) 2.8bn\((- 21\% \text{WoW})\) followed by \(+\) \(\) 986mn\((- 5\% \text{WoW})\) in the short end.

In other asset classes, Leveraged Loan funds \((+\) \(\) 823mn\(, + 28\% \text{WoW})\) , Munis \((+\) \(\) 916mn\(, - 68\% \text{WoW})\) and Equities \((+\) \(\) 9.6bn\(, +\) \(\) 10.6bn \text{WoW}) \text{saw inflows, while High Yield} (-\) \(\) 387mn\(continued to see outflows for a second week.

Lastly, our estimates suggest that HG dealer inventories \((>13m)\) have increased from the last Fed reported data and now stand at \(45\%\) of their 3m range and HY dealer inventories have also increased and now stand at \(69\%\) of their 3m range (Figure 3).

- The JULI spread was unchanged on Thursday at 88bp, while the yield fell by 3bp to \(5.26\%\) (Table 1).

- There was no High Grade Issuance on Thursday. WTD \(\) 3bn\(has been issued. MTD\) \ \(99bn\) has been issued. YTD supply totals \(\) 1092bn\(. Issuance in August has averaged\) \ \(93bn\) over the past four years.
- Bonds issued over the past 9 days are 2bp wider than at issuance on average (based on\)\\(20bn across 29 JULI eligible bonds), while the index overall is 3bp wider over the same time period.

- Trading activity in HG bonds was \(\) 41.8bn\(on Thursday (2w average\) \ \(30.6bn / day\) , YTD average \(\) 38.5bn/day). Dealers were net buyers of\)\\(2.5bn\) of bonds (1w avg \(\) 1bn/day buying, 3m avg \(\) 353mn/day selling). Dealers net bought \(\) 5.1bn\(of bonds from investors over the past 5 days and net bought\) \ \(5.3bn\) of bonds from investors over the past 10 days. \(17.4\%\) of trading yesterday was executed through Portfolio Trades and over the past 5 days this figure is \(15.8\%\) . Over the 5 day period \(\) 2.9bn\(of new HG bonds were issued.

- Our estimate of dealer net positions in corporate bonds \(>13\mathrm{m}\) increased by \(\) 851\mathrm{mn}$ on Thursday (this includes TRACE and ETF data). On the week this estimate of positions is up by \(\) 2bn\(to -\) \ \(2.2bn\) , which is at the \(45\%\) level in the 3m range. Within the last 3m range, positions are at the \(12\%\) level in the 1-5yr bucket, at the \(77\%\) level in the 5-10yr bucket, and at the \(73\%\) level in the \(10+\) yr bucket (Table 5).

- The 3s5s curve is trading at 15bp (100% of its 1m range), 5s10s is trading at 24bp (88% of its 1m range) and 10s30s is trading at 10bp (6% of its 1m range). Please see our Curveball: HG Credit Curve Opportunities for details on the bond pairs which comprise these curves and the steepest/flattest ones in each segment (Table 3).

- Our new Credit Relative Value Screen highlights several relationships which are out of line with their historical trading patterns: B3 US Leveraged Loans are tight to B2 US Leveraged Loans, CCC US Leveraged Loans are wide to B3 US Leveraged Loans, 10y A-rated bonds are wide to 10y AA Taxable Munis and 5y US HG bonds are wide to MBS Current Coupon.

- CDX.IG 5y index tightened by 0.2bp on Thursday to 50.1bp. CDX.IG performed in line with its underlying CDS on Thursday and is trading 1bp rich to its fair value (Table 7). Please see today's CDX.IG Analytics for more details.

- The 25 largest HG Credit ETFs had combined inflows of \(\) 278\mathrm{mn}$ on Thursday (0.10% of AUM). This compares to \(\) 1.6bn$ of inflows (0.59% of AUM) over the week and \(\) 10.8bn$ of inflows (4.07% of AUM) over the month.

- CDX.HY 5y index rallied by 5c/1bp on Thursday to \(\) 107.4/314\mathrm{bp}\(. CDX.HY performed in line with its underlying CDS on Thursday and is trading 31c/7bp rich to its fair value (Table 7). Please see today's CDX.HY Analytics for more details.
